Pairplot of continuous factors

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
data = pd.read_csv("C:/Users/dkirksey/Downloads/Admission_Predict.csv")
data.drop(['Research','Serial No.'],axis=1, inplace = True)
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize']=(2,2)
sns.pairplot(data, diag_kind='kde')
plt.show()

Chance of Admission appears to have a the strongest correlation with GRE.Score, TOEFL.Score, and CGPA.

Linear Regression Model

import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
## C:\Users\dkirksey\AppData\Roaming\Python\Python37\site-packages\sklearn\externals\joblib\externals\cloudpickle\cloudpickle.py:47: DeprecationWarning: the imp module is deprecated in favour of importlib; see the module's documentation for alternative uses
##   import imp
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
sns.set_style('darkgrid')
data = pd.read_csv("C:/Users/dkirksey/Downloads/Admission_Predict.csv")
reg = LinearRegression()
X = data[['GRE Score', 'TOEFL Score', 'SOP','CGPA','LOR ']]
y= data['Chance of Admit ']
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.3)
reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred = reg.predict(X_test)
print(pd.DataFrame(data=reg.coef_, columns=['Coefficients'], index=X.columns))
##              Coefficients
## GRE Score        0.003182
## TOEFL Score      0.003821
## SOP             -0.004410
## CGPA             0.102205
## LOR              0.024376
plt.gcf().clear()
plt.scatter(x=y_test, y=y_pred)
plt.xlabel('Y_test')
plt.ylabel('Y_pred')
plt.title('Model Evaluation')
plt.show()

Chance of admission is most affected by students cumulative GPA.
